There is currently limited evidence about the relationshipbetween e-cigarette use and COVID-19. However, existing evidence indicates thatelectronic nicotine delivery systems (ENDS) and electronic non-nicotinedelivery systems (ENNDS), more commonly referred to as e-cigarettes, areharmful and increase the risk of heart disease and lung disorders. Given thatthe COVID-19 virus affects the respiratory tract, e-cigarette use mayincrease the risk of infection or severity of outcomes due to COVID-19.    
